cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.CE, cs.DB 

This paper focuses on machine learning techniques for time series data, specifically in the context of electronic health record data. The use of deep learning models like LSTM networks suggests a focus on the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the application to healthcare data suggests a focus on cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and potentially cs.CE (Computational Epidemiology). The use of gradient boosting trees also suggests a focus on cs.DB (Databases) and potentially cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for their use in combining a large number of features.
